node.text: In this episode of #ChopItUp, Brandon Bryant and John Henry break down the absolutely enormous impact that Nipsey Hussle had on his community. But first, the guys go deep into Tiger's comeback at The Masters and why we live in a culture where winning solves everything. Then, Brandon and John take a look at the economics of #Coachella and identify some of the festival's missed business opportunities. Finally, they weigh the pros and cons of starting your own business versus launching a venture inside of a larger company.

node.text: Still riding the wave of the @Afro.tech conference in San Francisco. I had the chance to team up with @uber while in town to meet members of UberHue, their resource group for black employees, and attended a networking mixer at their HQ. Lots of great conversations and new relationships made - all focused on pushing the culture forward for people of color. My takeaways from this trip are be bold and speak on issues that can foster more inclusivity. People of color are creating products & companies in the tech space that are defining our future and we must be active + pursue conferences, events, companies, etc. that have purpose and are striving to make an impact #Whereto #ad #AllTheGreatMinds

node.text: #NYC · In partnership with @Uber I get a chance to show the behind the scenes of my passion for making custom garments at my suit shop in Brooklyn. The main reason why I stumbled into fashion is because I could not fit anything off the rack, so once I had a few coins in my pocket I went to work figuring out how to make my own clothes. Five years later I only wear clothes I designed myself. #Uber gives me the flexibility to grab fabrics, buttons, etc. from all over the city and head back to my suit shop + put it all together  #ad #DoorsAreAlwaysOpening!

#PHL · || #SmallWins || Over the years I have been disciplined and saved up to invest in real estate. At the end of 2019 I partnered with a good friend to invest in a townhouse in Philly. Well, the townhouse is almost finished (we had a few delays - such is life!) and we're getting ready to lease it to tenants. I am grateful to partner with @Bestbuy to capture some of these moments with my new camera! Swipe left to see a few before / future rendering photos of the townhouse.

Over the next few months as a #BestBuyPartner I will share more tech tools that help me capture / create milestones like the one today. Remember it's all about celebrating the small wins in life!  #Ad⠀

#CLE · || #Hennessy || Excited to announce my partnership with @hennessy I have always admired their brand from a far, the history the brand embodies. I decided to go with the refreshing, easy to make, Guava Hennesy Cocktail as my summer go to. I enjoy making specialty cocktails at home on the weekends, it gives me a chance to be creative, test out new ingredients and of course everyone loves a good bartender. Grab yourself a refreshing cocktail with Hennessy this summer (link in bio)! 

Guava Hennessy Cocktail 
	•	40 ml Hennessy Very Special 
	•	2 slices of strawberries
	•	1 lime wedge
	•	60 ml of guava juice 
Mash the strawberry and lime, then place the mixture in a cocktail shaker. Add the Hennessy Very Special and the ice, then shake. Filter into a cocktail glass and garnish with a slice of strawberries. 
 
For more recipes with Hennessy, head over to their website. Link in stories. 
Always enjoy drinks responsibly!
#HennessyVS #HennessyMix #Ad !⠀
--
#wallstreetpaper
Ph: @chietanak
